text: b"Bummer. I just discovered my health insurance doesn't cover Altoids."
b'Contrary to popular belief, not everybody was kung fu fighting. I was taking a nap.'
b'Right now my attention span is more like attention spam.'
b"I'm following @charliesheen. Someone has to do it."
b"I got a great review at work today. I guess this means they're expecting me to do some actual work now."
b"What's with these solar flares? Next it will be skinny jeans and flower print bell-bottoms. Imagine the effect on our electronica from that."
b'Lindsay Lohan may be in a Superman movie. It\'s called "Superman Gets Wasted, Steals Shit & Flashes His Junk While Exiting a Limo, Part 1."'
b'@punslingerr Omg. I actually do remember that one. Talk about a blast from the past!'
b'@punslingerr What?!? I thought YOU knew.'
b'@punslingerr I remember that one!'
b"It's fashion week in NYC. Time to break out the orange traffic cone headwear and airplane propeller shoulder pads."
b"I think I'm becoming addicted to home improvement shows. I may have to hit a few Boring Anonymous meetings."
b"Watching Wayne and Garth on SNL discussing their Winter's Bones. Party on."
b'You had me at Hello Kitty. #worstpickuplines'
b'Hey! Who replaced my facial features with those of Mrs. Potato Head while I was asleep?'
b'Who am I wearing this winter? Why, Kenny of South Park, of course.'
b'@joeschmitt "You Bastard \'11" works for me.'
b'This snow would be beautiful if it were somewhere else instead of here. Thank you sir may we have another?'
b'@RanGt Thank you. Missed you too and the rest of this looney bin.'
b'They say no 2 snowflakes are alike but I could swear I just saw a couple of them wearing THE SAME Dior gown a few of minutes ago.'
b'Yum! That 42" TV dinner sure hit the spot.'
b"So far I'm not too impressed with Skynet's dishwashing capabilities."
b"I'm so glad it's only 10 P.M. I still have several more responsibilities to shirk today."
b'I wish I had come with free shipping and handling.'
b'It looks like the zombies in this movie just ate at Taco Bell.'
b'@robertgdaniel At least it would melt some of this damn snow.'
b'I just took a really hot shower and now I look like I should melt some butter, put on a bib and have myself for dinner.'
b"It looks like the only exercise I'm going to get today is hunting for all the remotes I need to watch a DVD."
b'I like big buttermilk pancakes I cannot lie.'
b'Many years ago, Charlie Sheen was my co-pilot.'
b"I'm channeling my inner Lara Croft by walking on snow & ice with an untied shoelace. Cause that's how I roll. (Down the front steps. Ow.)"
b"I'll bet the Kardashians never have to clean the catbox."
b"Right now I'm totally winning at the game of Monotony."
b'@darthvader As you wish Your Evilness.'
b"The Bourne Ultimatum is on. This is the one where he finds out he's actually Wolverine."
b"I'll bet Hello Kitty never vomits on the carpeting."
b"I bought a new umbrella today. I'm pretty sure this happened because of the subliminal messages in that Rihanna song."
b'Sometimes I wish I were in dog years. Then I could have retired way before I even started working.'
b'Maybe Britney should try holding it against herself.'
b"I wish they'd turn the volume up in ads. It's difficult to hear their important messages over the sound of trillions of brain cells dying."
b'I passed a woman in the store who had really bad B.O. I made sure to secretly sniff my own before I mentally called her a pig.'
b'I just saw an ad for The Scooter Store. I ordered the one with the hemi and the flames painted on the sides.'
b"I'm waiting for a guy to come over and snowblow my back deck. Too bad this isn't a euphemism, especially since I have to pay for it."
b"I'm alternating between The Weather Channel and Teminator 3. More snow and a really bitchy cyborg are on the way."
b"My laptop hasn't crashed once today. I guess that stern talking-to and drop kick across the room did the trick."
b"@BecksWinter I know! I can't believe it either."
b'I feel like I should go to sleep now but I want to stay up to see how this movie ends. (Titanic)'
b"I find it makes you look more refined and delicate if you hold your pinky out while you're eating from a 1.5 qt. ice cream container."
b'@GringoQuixote Thank you. I missed my daily dose of twitter insanity.'
b'@oinkflap Under the huge mound of snow on my back deck. Nice to see you again Mr. Flap.'
b"Long term sleep deprivation can be fun. I like the hallucinations best when they aren't interrupted by commercials and pop-ups."
b"How come @JimCameron won't follow me back? Doesn't he know who I am?"
b'I think I might have an ear infection. This might be from constantly sticking my finger in it to check if I have an ear infection.'
b"@jen4coffee Thank you! Nice to see you again too. I haven't been here in a month. I think I overslept again."
b"It's also been so cold here this winter that my once formidable typing skills have been greatly diminished."
b"There's a dog barking outside. It'a been a very snowy winter here and I'm pretty sure it's one of the sled dogs I use to get to work."
b'My sincere thanks to everyone who made my holiday season so bright by not giving me anything even remotely resembling a fruitcake.'
b"@MentalVasectomy Hey Mental! Nice to meet you. How they hangin'?"
b"@EmmyMcLarty It's alive!"
b"My computer tried to call in sick. In no mood for that kind of insubordination this morning, I shot it. We're both better now."
b"Be back later. Gotta do more packing. By that I mean eat some Cap'n Crunch, watch TV and order my possessions to hurl themselves into boxes."
b"@kattcalls Either. Both. I'm not picky."
b"@jen4coffee We can share. That's what friends are for."
b'@smuuvvgroove Not soon enough unfortunately. :('
b"@jen4coffee Ok thanks! I'll send a cabana boy over for it in a few."
b"@kattcalls Thank you and yes it does mean that. I don't need no stinking relationship anyway. (Unless Hugh Jackman shows up on my doorstep.)"
b'I hate moving. What a shitty time for my teleportation unit to be in the shop for its 8,000,000 mile tune-up. Be afraid, be very afraid.'
b'@jen4coffee Thank you. Life goes on and it gets better. Especially if I can remember where I stashed those cabana boys.'
b"@Cheeky_Geek Thank you. Here's to looo-ooo-ooove!"
b'I just told myself "Not tonight, I have a headache" and I meant it.'
b"@MrErv That's what I'd like to know damn it!"
b'@juicymorsel @gneicco @BecksWinter Thanks guys. It sucks but I\'ll be putting out my neon "NEXT!" sign on my new lawn at my new house soon.'
b'My 8 yr. relationship has ended with a whimper instead of a bang. Alas, now I have to move. Traumatically, this means off the couch too.'
b"@JuicyJones I've always thought you look totally cool. (I look totally cool too)."
b'I like to live dangerously. The other day day I left home without my American Express card. #thuglife'
b"@dentednj Thank you. Or maybe some much needed collagen injections while they're at it."
b'James Bond movie #28: Sharktopussy.'
b"I'm watching a pretty good movie. (300) It features a bunch of guys flaunting their gigantic, sweaty, partially naked acting abilities."
b"@itsdonnaok That's good to know. I'll check my look in the mirror."
b'@punslingerr Yay!'
b'@punslingerr I think you should watch some of each so your brain can combine the two later. :)'
b'Why does our universe have to get stuck with all the crappy TV programming? And why is my typing so bad I almost misspelled TV?'
b"Sometimes I have the nagging suspicion that my parents might have been right and I really don't know what the hell I'm doing."
b"@brittybyte Thank you. Good to see you again. No wonder things haven't been *normal*. I haven't been here in a month."
b'@amyzesbaugh I missed you too! Damned dwarves.'
b"I've had some stress, turmoil and upheaval in my life lately. Aren't these some of the 7 deadly sins/dwarves?"
b'When you have a brain fart, are you supposed to say excuse me or should you just blame it on the person next to you?'
b'I double dog dare the Kardashians to try to keep up with me.'
b"I'm having some pain in my rotator cuff. There goes my promising pitching career."
b'Some wiseguy must have turned the gravitational pull up to high again today.'
b'Last night I dreamed about an imaginary guy writing profound burrito haiku for his girlfriend. I know twitter dream symbolism when I see it.'
b"@badbanana Personally, I'm outraged that I am also bored."
b'I went outside to watch the meteor showers last night. I only saw 1 in the whole 5 minutes I was out there. I want my money back.'
b"It's a good thing I don't have my own reality show because my Nielsen ratings would be in the negative numbers right now."
b"I have to go to a bridal (bridle?) shower tomorrow. It's either a pre-wedding party or some lame thing involving Sarah Jessica Parker."
b'I lost my wallet today. Thankfully, I found it intact before someone could use my credit card or steal my identities.'
b'@zombot It was in a large field! With a large crane, some large men and a homemade castle. It was most medievally excellent.'
b"Today I saw some people using a crane to assemble a 60' tall trebuchet and now I have a severe case of large, lethal lawn ornament envy."
b'Hello weekend. Wanna play doctor?'
b'@punslingerr It was getting a little too smelly. It had to go.'
b'@punslingerr Every week is TV Land\'s "Jump the Shark" week as far as I can tell.'
b'@randomisms I actually borrowed one from a friend. Alas, it was only temporary.'
b"It's Shark Week again already? It seems like only yesterday I put the decorations away from last year."
b"I haven't been on twitter for a few days. I hope everyone misbehaved appropriately while I was away."
b'I just heard some disturbing news. Barney is not extinct yet.'
b"I'm busy playing an extra in the movie of my life."
b'FYI-Tomorrow (Monday) is International Toilet Paper Your Workplace Day.'
b'My younger, cooler self just called and wants to know when exactly did I become such a dork.'
b'@Capsaholic I know! Creepy but fascinating.'
b"There's a movie on with Christopher Walken in it. As in all his other movies, he's playing Christopher Walken."
b"Did you know you can buy toilet water at perfume counters? I'm going to make a shitload of $ at my next yard sale."
b'Comic-Con was all fun and games until someone got 5 of their 11 eyeballs poked out.'
b"@HindSight5050 I think you've inspired me. Slurp."
b"@HindSight5050 What was I thinking? I'll skip the repeat part."
b"I'm drinking coffee and making a list of my goals for today. Here it is: 1.Twitter. 2. Nap 3.Snack. 4.Watch TV.  Lather, rinse, repeat."
b'I just saw a recent picture of Keanu Reeves. It looks like he has a rabid Chia Pet growing on/out of his lower face.'
b'If I suspect someone is asking me a question because they want something from me, I like to answer "I don\'t know", especially if I do.'
b'@ThoughtSnot Either. Not a grown-up or a princess in sight.'
b"It's a good thing I didn't want to be a princess when I grew up because I'm about as far from that as it gets."
b'Sometimes my imagination could use a restraining order.'
b"My truck's in the shop today. Hopefully I can come up with the ransom money needed to get it back later."
b"We never get bank robbers in cool disguises like @darthvader. Here in NH they're mostly dressed as toothless cows."
b'@badbanana Apparently those first class cabin drinks have quite the kick.'
b'@bklynMF I loved it! I hope they make a sequel so I can bitch and complain about how much it sucks compared to the original.'
b'I saw Inception last night. My few remaining brain cells are exhausted. What a kick.'
b"Today's personal problem: The scrolly thing isn't working on my laptop."
b"Trying to figure out what size aquarium I'd need for a school of endorphins."
b'@yelyahwilliams Obviously, the people in those ads have never heard the song "Don\'t worry, be happy."'
b"@robertgdaniel I'm not sure....I think we were both out of the room that time."
b'@robertgdaniel I have Ant Farm envy.'
b'When I was a kid I had an educational little thing called an Ant Farm. I still have it, only now I refer to it as My House.'
b"@gneicco I knew there had to be a logical explanation. (Besides the Occam's Razor of insanity of course.)"
b"I wonder what this is a sign of. I just talked to the cat but the cat wasn't even in the room."
b'Preparing for the arrival of Monday by watching The Boondock Saints. I feel better already.'
b'Lethal Cooties is more like it Mel.'
b'The microwave is beeping at me. I suspect it wants to be more than just friends.'
b"I wish I could take Will Smith to work with me. I bet he'd show the malevolent alien life-forms I work for a thing or two."
b'@HindSight5050 In my eyes, you will always be a starship captain. Possibly even an admiral.'
b'@mnik :)'
b'@MDuette I love duct tape. You too!'
b'@MDuette Dude-ette!'
b'I was all set to watch something cultural and intellectually stimulating. Fortunately, I realized Men in Black was on in the nick of time.'
b'Hey, someone won. Celebrate irresponsibly.'
b'@blueblazerreg @juicymorsel Bring us a shrubbery.'
b'@juicymorsel @blueblazerreg Also, I\'m thinking I like the sound of "I\'ve got a bad case of the microbursts" as well.'
b"I've decided to blame all my future bouts of bitchiness and bad attitudes on solar flares."
b'We got a great table at the wedding reception today. You know the one. The loud/obnoxious/scary one no one else wants to go near. Win.'
b"I went to  a friend's wedding today. I didn't catch the bouquet but I did manage to not get toilet paper stuck to my shoe in the restroom."
b"I haven't had internet access for a few days and I was about to gnaw off my own power cord."
b"I'm sure glad I didn't live in the days of our Founding Fathers. Those wigs look really uncomfortable and unflattering as hell."
b"What's with the boring historical shows on TV? Don't they know 3 day weekends are what ancient Twilight Zone marathons are for?"
b'4 out of 5 of my personalities agree: This was the best day in a long time. (The 5th slept through everything.)'
b"I've been in a really bad mood lately due to work related stress. But it's nothing that a well-timed mutiny and a keelhauling won't cure."
b'I now know there really is a Hell because it has finally dawned on me that I work there.'
b'You give love a Bad Request.'
b"Once upon a time I logged onto twitter and it wasn't having any issues. The End. Hahaha. Everyone knows a fairy tale when they see it."
b'I think I just broke my toe by running into a piece of furniture. There go my chances of winning the World Cup.'
b'@Sammmmeh :)'
b"Man, I really hate it when things are crawling on me and I didn't ask them to."
b"@punslingerr Or it might be Die Hard XVIII. It's hard to tell."
b"I'm watching a movie with Bruce Willis in it. It's the one with all the explosions."
b'There are ants in the bathroom. I hope they remember to flush.'
b"Once again another weekend has flown by. At least they don't shit on your head like weekdays."
b'@BecksWinter :)'
b'Fondly remembering my 1st day on twitter a year ago. Stayed up all night reading tweets my niece, a couple of bots and @aplusk. Good times.'
b"Happy Father's Day to all you dad dudes. Grill it and drill it."
b'Someone rototilled my hair while I was asleep.'
b'@darthvader Hopefully not another unfashionably wide Tie Fighter either.'
b'My animation is loading......Please wait.'
b"Big thanks to everyone who #FF'd and RT'd me. My life for you."
b"Instead of going through all the trouble of folding this fitted sheet, I'm just going to roll it up into a ball and set it on fire."
b'@MDuette Righteo! You must be psychic.'
b'@MDuette Quarantine? As in: This movie should have been.'
b'There are people running around like screaming, arm-flailing lunatics in this movie. They must have read the script.'
b"I just hit my shin real hard with the vacuum. It's a good thing I have a vast repertoire of pain-relieving swear words at my disposal."
b"@kattcalls Brilliant! I wish I'd thought of that."
b"If I could go back in time and change something from my childhood I think I'd cheat more while playing Monopoly."
b'My boyfriend is helping a friend move. This is my sitting on the couch tweeting and watching TV sympathy tweet for him.'
b"I'm too tired to riot."
b"How do they they know these fingers are from Vienna? It's not like they have little Austrian flags on them or anything."
b"I worked my ass off today. That's why they pay someone else the big bucks."
b"It's a tearing off mattress tags kind of day."
b'So far, my proudest achievement is getting out of bed this morning.'
b'Bulletin: Yesterday a partially dismembered workplace printer was found display down in a pool of magenta. I may or may not be a suspect.'
b'Maybe BP should try jiggling the handle. It works for my toilet.'
b"@punslingerr That's exactly what I was thinking!"
b'Again with the fail whale @twitter? I want a divorce.'
b"This weekend wasn't long enough. I'm sending it back to the kitchen. Waiter!"
b"I don't have control of the remote right now and my boredom level is approaching critical mass."
b'@TheBosha I love that but try to indulge in it only accidentally.'
b'Manhandling some manhandles.'
b"I'm folding underwear even though this has always seemed kind of pointless to me. Especially if someone's still wearing it."
b"I was so busy today I forgot to eat again. Even my usual Sunday donut. It's like I don't know myselves anymore."
b'I spent the day planting a big flower garden. It looks great and so do I because my personal dirt coverage is down to the molecular level.'
b"If I were feeling just a little more energetic, I'd be classified as comatose right now."
b"It's raining on my reality and I forgot my umbrella-ella-ella."
b"I'm starving so I'm going to eat something unhealthy but delicious which will be completely counteracted if I also eat a piece of celery."
b"I've been on here about a half hour so far today and I haven't seen a single fail whale. Is Twitter broken?"
b'@juicymorsel Way to think outside the penalty box.'
b"@notmick I'm so relieved. I think."
b'@bluedream420 Word.'
b"I see there's another big sporting event taking place. I sure hope someone wins it."
b'Hit me with the fail whale one more time.'
b'RIP Twitter.....again.'
b'@DarwynsTheory Thank you for flying ZombieAir.'
b"Thank you for the #FF's and RT's. As usual, the check's in the mail."
b'@OGOchoCinco That sounds like fun. Can I try that at home?'
b"I just realized I've been walking around with a rock in my shoe for a couple of hours. It must have escaped from my head."
b'My planets are out of alignment. It may be time for an undergarment update.'
b'@avi1111 @kattcalls Beam us up Scotty.'
b'BP also let the dogs out.'
b"@rejecter They should be thankful they don't live here. Otherwise they'd be screwed like the rest of us."
b"@Sammmmeh Yeah! That's what I meant-tomorrow. ;)"
b'Sometimes it seems like my attention span needs to be put on an endangered species list.'
b'Gotta go. Those terrifying Dopplar bands of psychedelia are almost upon us.'
b'@kattcalls Totally and Toto too.'
b'@redneck_trash Maybe in my yard!'
b'@kattcalls Flying C-OW! manure?'
b'A rare tornado watch is in effect for our state. (NH) I hope all the cows here have basements.'
b"@BitterOldPunk Thanks! I don't know what I'd do without you. Now where did I put that Bag of Holding. Hmmm."
b'@RadishSpirit Shhh! :)'
b"I can't find my cloak of invisibility."
b'@Sammmmeh Back at you. Happy Smurfday-yesterday.'
b'These thunderstorms are cramping my questionable style and this lightning is even worse for my complexion than fluorescent lighting.'
b"Who wants to come over and do my housework, my laundry and run some errands? It's not just a job, it's an adventure."
b"I'm so glad I'm on Twitter right now because my boyfriend's choice of TV programming completely sucks ass."
b"I'm going to live dangerously and try this at home."
b"I'm being eaten by mosquitoes. At least they brought their own condiments and utensils."
b'My other tweet is a typo.'
b"This was such a well-behaved Monday I'm going to give it some extra treats and let it sleep on the couch tonight."
b"To whoever/whatever is responsible for speeding up time during long weekends: It wasn't funny the first time."
b"I'm going to a cookout soon. I hope it gets a little outta control so I'll have some shenanigans/debauchery to tweet about later."
b'I like how Twitter is doing Trending Topics from neighboring galaxies now.'
b'@punslingerr :)'
b'Warning: This movie contains violence and sexual content. Thanks for the heads up. I was about to change the channel.'
b'@zombot Yes, as long as you have your pinky extended. It looks classier that way.'
b'@RaminHossaini Or maybe Mewt button?'
b"@FussySaffa Every damn day. That's why I love this little corner of Twitter."
b'Sometimes I wish cats came with remotes.'
b'@broast Happy Smurfday! May today bring you much Loretta Lynn, 0 Lady Gaga and a hot new boyfriend. Go ahead and be crazy.'
b'I have set my fan and my brain to "oscillate."'
b'This Star Wars movie has Jar Jar Binks in it. No wonder there was a rebellion.'
b'@robertgdaniel What was I not thinking?'
b'Last but not least really means last. And least.'
b'@rachyrach1 Hahaha! Hence the lobster suit.'
b'@rachyrach1 Maybe he rents himself out to other lobster deprived states?'
b"@SilkPillow That's even more impressive. I'm starting to get hungry."
b'@rachyrach1 Close, NH.'
b'I just saw a guy dressed as a lobster waving his claws at pointing, snickering passersby. How come other people get all the good jobs?'
b"I'm at Home Depot but I can't seem to locate any homes or depots. You'd think they would've stocked up for the holiday weekend."
b"What happened to the sunshine we were supposed to have here today? I'm suing the weather department for false advertising."
b"I'm constructing something out of tin foil and duct tape. It may or may not have shoulder pads and an antenna."
b'@crankfetter They bravely gave their all.'
b'@JeeNeeBee Not for too much longer. They have a terribly short shelf life around me.'
b"@MeanMartini How rude! I'm so sorry. I'll send some over now."
b"Big thanks to everyone for the #FF's, RT's, lists etc. And for the donuts."
b"I just saw a former co-worker here at Walmart. I'm so glad we had the good sense to pretend we didn't see each other."
b"I'm at Walmart on a rare Friday night off work. Something is wrong with this picture but I haven't been able to connect all the dots yet."
b"Oh no! Spencer Pratt and Heidi Montag have broken up. Now I'll have to go through all the trouble of despising them individually."
b"I didn't think it was possible but I've had too much coffee today. I have set myself to vibrate AND ring."
b"I just found out I don't have to work today so I'm free for the next 4 days! I'm beside myself with happiness. We make quite the threesome."
b"My Trending Topics have disappeared. It's about time."
b"I can barely contain my excitement. SATC2  is finally out. I haven't looked forward to not seeing a film this much since SATC1."
b'@MrErv 1 meeellion dollars!'
b'Today seems like a good day to hold myself hostage.'
b'@dootsiebug I am SO following that. Lol'
b'This oil spill is a terrible reality show.'
b"I hope today is Wednesday. I couldn't take another Monday or Tuesday this week."
b"@beautifl1s It's so cool."
b'I love my AC even though it told me it only wants to be friends.'
b"@KirstensDesk Ha! Thanks, I'm glad someone else got that. I should have known you would."
b"It's a cookbook!!!"
b'@krislynch Probably not. :)'
b'I saw some fireflies here last night. I wonder if it makes it easier to get a date if your butt lights up everywhere you go.'
b'When I see NEW! IMPROVED! on a label, it seems to me that they are just admitting the old, unimproved version was real crap.'
b"@punslingerr You're welcome and thank you back. :)"
b'@punslingerr Nice job! You get way more than a golf/tennis clap for that.'
b"It seems like someone's missing here and I'm not too sure it isn't me."
b'@mikey_m00n That was exquisitely bad.'
b"Dead from New Hampshire, it's Saturday night!"
b'I really like the way big bubble wrap makes that kind of machine gun sound when you roll over it with a chair.'
b'@Sammmmeh I love you more! :)'
b"I'm so sleep deprived I think I'm hallucinating. It's all fun and games until someone gets their eyeball poked out by a 3 headed unicorn."
b'My niece graduated from high school today. I graduated from merely fast to lightening speed in wolfing down the free food afterward.'
b'I just noticed that my hands are dirty. No wonder my finger puppets look so disturbed.'
b"Somewhere in an alternate universe there's an alternate me who loves Mondays. That me is definitely on drugs."
b"I'm watching Hannah Montana. I think it's the lap dancing with the gay dude episode."
b'I hope the dinosaurs were all wearing clean underwear when the big one hit.'
b"I've decided to stay home tonight. The paparazzi and my legions of fans will be terribly disappointed, but who said life was fair anyway?"
b'My home page just expanded into infinity again. Thanks for the lame special effects again Twitter.'
b"I don't even have the energy to feel guilty about all the responsibilities I'm shirking right now."
b"I'm supposed to go out dancing tonight. I'd probably feel more enthusiastic about doing this if I were dead."
b'@gneicco Oops. My bad.'
b"I'm watching a Will Smith drama called Seven Pounds. I'm having a hard time following the storyline due to a lack of aliens/explosions."
b"This must be the part where I make some comment about being glad it's the weekend and by the time I'm finished typing this it's over."
b'@MDuette Thanks. I knew I could count on you.'
b"I was loving the song with the great beat in the lunchroom at work today when I realized it was the dishwasher running. It's great to be me."
b'@MDuette Lol. Feels like 400 PSI in there. Ow.'
b"@nikkipariah Yes, I think it's contagious unfortunately."
b'My sinuses need an exorcism.'
b"There's a documentary on about Frank Perdue . It tastes like chicken."
b"I'm exhausted from mowing the lawn today. Who knew turning a steering wheel and reaching for a beverage in the cupholder could be so tiring."
b"A big THANK YOU for the #FF's, RT's, lists etc."
b'I just took  a really long, hot shower. I now resemble a large red prune minus the social skills and sex appeal.'
b"Happy Mother's Day. I got you this tweet. Enjoy."
b"I'm at the movie theater about to see Iron Man 2. My inner fangirl is overly excited and needs to get a life."
b"It's never too late to not give a shit."
b'Taking the dork for a walk.'
b"I thought for sure by now I'd have a Jetson's style Rosie the robot housekeeper. #Futurefail"
b"Watching the original Superman movie because after typing this tweet I'm way too exhausted to reach the the remote & change the channel."
b"@Sammmmeh Awww. You're so sweet. :)"
b'My boyfriend is busy clearing out the beaver dams that were clogging our culverts. Not a euphemism but fun to say.'
b'@zombot Always a pleasure to see your avatar. Especially that light saber?'
b'Hey Twitter did you miss me? I missed you but only by a couple of inches.'
b'I love Cheetos and their flourescent radioactive orange residue.'
b'I move that we make Cinco De Mayo a national, federal US holiday so that we can help Mexico celebrate it with a day off from work.'
b'Sometimes it sucks to live in the boonies. With my binoculars all I can see are beautiful scenery & wildlife. Not a naked neighbor in sight.'
b"@donchiefnerd I know, and there's only so much I'm willing to compromise on in this relationship. I think that movie would be the end of us."
b"Trying to to convince my bf to watch a movie so I don't have to watch yet another episode of America's Deadliest Ice Road AxMen or whatever."
b"So, the Kentucky Derby is on and no one has made any comments pro or con about SJP's outfit? WTF?"
b'I love this time of year when the weeds in my garden are actively growing and I get to actively annihilate them with my trusty lightsaber.'
